Every writer is different and may want something that the next writer doesn&#039;t. The worst thing you can do is assume what they want. If you aren&#039;t willing to ask, at least pay attention when they talk about their writing. Chances are they will indirectly tell you want they want/need.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://wordcounter.net/blog/2014/06/02/1020_20-helpful-and-fun-products-for-writers.html#comments/9777">Pethra</a>.</p>
<p>Every writer is different and may want something that the next writer doesn&#8217;t. The worst thing you can do is assume what they want. If you aren&#8217;t willing to ask, at least pay attention when they talk about their writing. Chances are they will indirectly tell you want they want/need.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
