This is the best advice in the comment section, Ask. It&#039;s far better to know what the writer wants than to try and guess what he or she might want. I&#039;ve never understood why people have such a difficult time asking  writers what they need or want. Most have a long list they are more than willing to share.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://wordcounter.net/blog/2014/06/02/1020_20-helpful-and-fun-products-for-writers.html#comments/9777">Pethra</a>.</p>
<p>This is the best advice in the comment section, Ask. It&#8217;s far better to know what the writer wants than to try and guess what he or she might want. I&#8217;ve never understood why people have such a difficult time asking  writers what they need or want. Most have a long list they are more than willing to share.</p>
